==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dioxide
<hw>Di*ox"ide</hw> <pr>(?; 104)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>di-</ets> + <ets>oxide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>An oxide containing two atoms of oxygen in each
molecule; binoxide.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An oxide containing but one
atom or equivalent of oxygen to two of a metal; a suboxide.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Carbon dioxide</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Carbonic
acid</cref>, under <er>Carbonic</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dioxindol</ent>⟦br⟧
